On behalf of a leading international school we are recruiting to a permanent Music Teacher vacancy.In order to join this superb English curriculum school you will need to be a graduate in Music who possesses qualified teacher status and have over two years' experience teaching music within a UK based or overseas English curriculum school music to GCSE and A Level standard.An enthusiastic and innovative approach to your work is essential combined with an outstanding understanding, knowledge and passion for music. You will be required to teach all ages and even stretch year 13 pupils applying to leading schools around the globe to study music! The school boasts an excellent music department which offers both quality and range in its academic and extra-curricular activities to its pupils. A competitive tax free salary is offered based on the schools own teaching scales - benefits include medical insurance, terminal gratuity, accommodation allowance and relocation as well as an annual return airline ticket. Interviews for this position will take place in London Mid May - in the first instance please forward your CV for immediate consideration.
